#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/gather_data_sampling.rst:4
msgid "GDS - Gather Data Sampling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/gather_data_sampling.rst:6
msgid ""
"Gather Data Sampling is a hardware vulnerability which allows unprivileged "
"speculative access to data which was previously stored in vector registers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/gather_data_sampling.rst:10
msgid "Problem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/gather_data_sampling.rst:11
msgid ""
"When a gather instruction performs loads from memory, different data "
"elements are merged into the destination vector register. However, when a "
"gather instruction that is transiently executed encounters a fault, stale "
"data from architectural or internal vector registers may get transiently "
"forwarded to the destination vector register instead. This will allow a "
"malicious attacker to infer stale data using typical side channel techniques "
"like cache timing attacks. GDS is a purely sampling-based attack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/gather_data_sampling.rst:19
msgid ""
"The attacker uses gather instructions to infer the stale vector register "
"data. The victim does not need to do anything special other than use the "
"vector registers. The victim does not need to use gather instructions to be "
"vulnerable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/gather_data_sampling.rst:24
msgid ""
"Because the buffers are shared between Hyper-Threads cross Hyper-Thread "
"attacks are possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/gather_data_sampling.rst:28
msgid "Attack scenarios"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/gather_data_sampling.rst:29
msgid ""
"Without mitigation, GDS can infer stale data across virtually all permission "
"boundaries:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/gather_data_sampling.rst:32
msgid ""
"Non-enclaves can infer SGX enclave data Userspace can infer kernel data "
"Guests can infer data from hosts Guest can infer guest from other guests "
"Users can infer data from other users"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/gather_data_sampling.rst:38
msgid ""
"Because of this, it is important to ensure that the mitigation stays enabled "
"in lower-privilege contexts like guests and when running outside SGX "
"enclaves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/gather_data_sampling.rst:41
msgid ""
"The hardware enforces the mitigation for SGX. Likewise, VMMs should  ensure "
"that guests are not allowed to disable the GDS mitigation. If a host erred "
"and allowed this, a guest could theoretically disable GDS mitigation, mount "
"an attack, and re-enable it."
msgstr ""

